        "Win rate and reward-to-risk sit on a seesaw, and your system just needs the combination to clear zero with room to spare. If your average win equals your average loss, you need better than 50 percent to profit. If your winners are twice your losers, you only need better than 33.3 percent. Trend followers live at 35 to 45 percent win rates with big winners, while premium sellers live at 70 to 90 percent with small winners and have to be ruthless about capping the rare loss. Neither shape is the right one. The only wrong shape is unprofitable.",
        "This is where the game film from episode two pays off, because your journal is the box score that makes these numbers computable. Calculate expectancy per setup, not just overall, since a healthy-looking account can be one strong play quietly subsidizing a hidden loser. And respect the sample size. Expectancy from 15 trades is a rumor. From 50 it is a hypothesis. From 100-plus it starts to become a fact you can build on.",
